included.description:
- Defined the user model and designed the interactions for a travel-based e-commerce app with a user-centered design process, and launched the app in Apple Store

- Conducted field research to observe and understand shopping behaviors in physical retail stores, generating design concepts for travel-centered e-commerce activities

- Created personas and customer journey to identify and prioritize core app features

- Created wireframes, user flows, and process flows to generate app logics, screen flow and page interface design 

- Used Appsee (an App analytics tool) and Google Analytics to remotely analyzed user session recordings, touch heatmaps, and other metrics of the app performance to optimize the app experience

included.description:
- Designed and launched a responsive B2C home security e-commerce website for home8 brand
Gaining traction of 135k website users with a 2.3% conversion rate and revenue of 450K in the first 6 months.

- Designed & optimized shopping flow, lead-gen and on-page optimization 
Bringing up home8 website conversion rate by 54%, signup rate by 17x, and pageviews by 32% and session length by 19%; analyzed and compared multiple marketing channelsâ ROIs to identify high traffic generators.

- Made improvements on app and websites by incorporating new features 
Including redesigning flow to support multi-location feature in home8 B2C app, ran A/B tests to identify better performing design solutions, and redesigning B2B MivaTek website for cloud solutions and IoT platform.

- Identified user feedback and implemented design optimization
Regarding home8 online shopping funnel, product offerings, and KPI-based website performance by designing user research plans and guides, analyzing user feedback and behaviors in analytics report.

- Worked with a team of 6, collaborated with cross-functions, and reported results to the management team
Led daily stand-ups, team brainstorms, design sprints and delivering weekly marketing performance reports to the management team.

(with previous working experience in GfK) 
- Provided StubHub with multi-screen research findings and actionable design recommendations about US usersâ tickets buying behavior across devices (on desktop, mobile web, iOS/Android mobile app), based on a 3-month qualitative and quantitative usability study using eye-tracking 

- Provided Walmart with customer insights about Chinese usersâ behaviors and attitudes and competitive analysis towards e-commerce and online shopping, from a 3-month UX research conducted for Walmart in multiple tiers of cities in China

- Provided Amazon.cn with findings of mobile and desktop shopping behaviors and patterns of Chinese users through a usability study 

- Provided Shopbop with a thorough understanding about userâs expectations, navigation pattern, decision-making process with online shopping, userâs interaction with detailed UI components, and test acceptance of certain concepts.
